                            <comment id="408837" author="pjones" created="Sat, 23 Mar 2024 15:55:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.16&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="408796" author="gerrit" created="Sat, 23 Mar 2024 06:11:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Oleg Drokin &amp;lt;green@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54320/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54320/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17623&quot; title=&quot;sanity-scrub: ASSERTION(debug_buf == string_buf) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17623&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17623&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: save msg_fn pointer to avoid race&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 02fc9e89775fe7f16d0aa78e369fec6313fec411&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="406781" author="gerrit" created="Thu, 7 Mar 2024 22:27:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54320&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54320&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17623&quot; title=&quot;sanity-scrub: ASSERTION(debug_buf == string_buf) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17623&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17623&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: save msg_fn pointer to avoid race&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 7b06be562a4da9c73d4fd74a9f46a2962fdab987&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="406729" author="adilger" created="Thu, 7 Mar 2024 16:42:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any thoughts on the best way to fix this, short of reverting the patch?  On the one hand, logging that &lt;tt&gt;cfs_fail_check_set()&lt;/tt&gt; was hit is less useful than printing which function called &lt;tt&gt;cfs_fail_check_set()&lt;/tt&gt;, but this also is not critical functionality to have. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think having an LASSERT() in the debug logging is great, since that is adding a failure for what would otherwise be a relatively harmless error. Should the __LASSERT() call be replaced by code that just handles this difference properly (use longer or shorter of two buffer lengths?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="406722" author="bzzz" created="Thu, 7 Mar 2024 15:56:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this is introduced with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14518&quot; title=&quot;allow slow request processing to be removed from health check&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14518&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14518&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: print CFS_FAIL_CHECK() location:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
-                       LCONSOLE_INFO(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;*** cfs_fail_loc=%x, val=%u***\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
-                                     id, value);
+                       CDEBUG_LIMIT_LOC(file, func, line,
+                                        (quiet &amp;amp;&amp;amp; failed_once) ?
+                                               D_INFO : D_CONSOLE,
+                                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;*** cfs_fail_loc=%x, val=%u***\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
+                                        id, value);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;basically we have a race where different threads reset msgdata-&amp;gt;msg_fn to own function so it can change during libcfs_debug_msg() runtime&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
